      <byline class="print_byline">By Stuart Elliott</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Elliott, Stuart</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Emap Communications acquires Cannes Lions International Advertising Festival from WJB Chiltern Trust Co (Jersey) Ltd; SMG Play, video game marketing unit of Starcom MediaVest Group, opens Starcom Play in Hong Kong to handle business in Asia; Starcom MediaVest is part of Publicis Groupe (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Emap Communications, London, the business-to-business publisher and events organizer unit of Emap, acquired the Cannes Lions International Advertising Festival, the annual creative advertising awards program held each June in Cannes, France, from the WJB Chiltern Trust Co. (Jersey) Ltd. Although terms were not disclosed, reports in Europe estimated the price at $100 million.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Emap Communications, London, the business-to-business publisher and events organizer unit of Emap, acquired the Cannes Lions International Advertising Festival, the annual creative advertising awards program held each June in Cannes, France, from the WJB Chiltern Trust Co. (Jersey) Ltd. Although terms were not disclosed, reports in Europe estimated the price at $100 million.</p>
        <p>SMG Play, Chicago, the video game marketing unit of the Starcom MediaVest Group, opened Starcom Play in Hong Kong to handle business in Asia. Starcom MediaVest is part of the Publicis Groupe.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
